annotation.TEXT: And one more springboard sprite and parakoopa for good measure.
And we have an underwater version of 6-2! Unfortunately, I don't think there are any world 1 pipe exit pointers in this level, so all of the pipe exits will just reset the level, like this.
Now for 1-Z (9-3, perhaps)!
I'm guessing yes, except something wherever midpoint was caused the game to lock up. Nuts. Guess I'll have to do some time travelling again.
Uh, oh. New potential problem. I forgot about this hole in the ceiling here. And there's no springboard nearby to let me get back up. I'm gonna have to take the lower route here.
D'oh! I thought I'd hit the 6 there.
Sorry this is so slow, but I'm almost at the goal.
Hello, and welcome back to yet another episode of New Strange Mario Bros.! I did think of something I hadn't tried yet in this hack, which I'll get to as soon as the game resets on me again here.
Nice, it's an underwater version of 1-4! And, I believe that... yep, there's a spring near the start that'll let me bounce onto the roof!
And now, I go over here, and enter the first warp zone pipe before the "Welcome to warp zone" message appears. Yep, it's the minus world!
Okay, whatever. That Blooper can live.
Hey there, burnt color-changing parakoopa.
...Well, that sucks. And I've backed up and retried this part a few times, and it always crashed here.
Okay, I'm going to get on the roof now so that I can access this level's flagpole.
A castle and a staircase? Is there a flagpole up ahead?
Ah, yep! As expected, it's a copy of 2-2/7-2. However, this time, the pipe exit doesn't work, and instead resets the level.
Interestingly, there's a fish generator here. Fortunately, they're not of the flying cheepo variety!
Even if I were to get over the wall now, I doubt I could get anywhere meaningful before time expires.
Wow, there sure are some odd enemy placements here so far...
DOUBLE KILL!
Whoa, this is different. There's a lava or red water background, but this isn't a swimming level.
Alright, let's try this again, but intentionally avoid earning fireworks this time...

Huh, there was an extra springboard sprite at the top of the screen there. SMB's springboards behave weirdly if there's multiple springboard sprites on screen at once, pulling Mario down more than they should.

...Well, that sucks. Unfortunately, the game crashed yet again. And I can't think of any other accessible worlds I haven't yet visited in this hack, so I hope you all enjoyed watching me play New Strange Mario Bros.! Bye!

Oh, no... World 1-Space (9-4) put me in this underwater "bonus" room, which has those dreaded flying cheepos! Well, I guess this gives me a chance to see the entirety of this room, since I always died in it on my previous visits!
Space-time rewind count: 21
Alright, I'm back to when I just emptied out this multi-coin block. Let's tackle that wall again.

Dang. I can't do it. I even tried using tool-assistance there, but still no luck. Mario can clip slightly into the wall, but the "suck"tion pulls him right back out, so I think it's impossible. That sucks...

Uh, oh. Lakitu decided to show up. Fortunately for me, he seems to be having trouble tossing any spinies for some reason, and there's this convenient row of bricks I can use to reach him. Just gotta watch out for the uber fire bar.
So, there's one other world that I can think of in this hack that I haven't actually tried yet.
Toasty!
Interestingly, that quadruple stomp was worth 100+400+800+2000.
Umm... There's a block. And here's some bricks.
Game crash count: 4
First, I'm gonna make my way to 1-1's bonus room...
Hi, Goombas. Bye, Goombas.
Hey there, Australian koopa.
Game crash count: 5
Almost got a spiny on my brain there.
And, world -1 is now complete!
Somehow, I figured that was gonna be a multi-coin block. (Of course, it could've certainly had nothing, or held a power up, star, 1-up, or vine.)
Okay, whew! Mario's stomps don't work underwater in SMB1 and SMB3 for whatever dumb reason, so landing on a koopa here would've taken away my burninating power.
Whoa, two close calls there: The podoboo that I barely dodged, and the platform that tried to pull me even deeper into the nether.

Ooh, world -3 is an overworld version of 3-4! Nice! I was getting sick of the water levels! (SMB tends to favor giving the player underwater versions of levels most of the time when you're outside of the usual 8 worlds for some reason.)
Nuts. I caught on the wall once early on, but failed to jump at the right time. Also, Lakitu's back, and he's successfully tossing spinies this time!
There's another springboard sprite and a moving platform. Also, the game hasn't reset on me here yet.
Yo, what's up, Bullet Bill?
I wonder if that platform's a fake... Well, I guess we'll never know.
Space-time rewind count: 22
Nuts. I was thinking that isolated one might've been another multi-coin block.
Toasty!
Oh, wow. I didn't take any special actions to try and prevent the game reset here. I just played normally totally expecting it to reset like usual, but it didn't this time!
Alright, can I maybe use the left edge of the screen to help me get back up onto the roof here?
This could be huge! I'll be able to see 1-Y, and possibly 1-Z and the levels beyond the end of the alphabet!
Let's just hope I can bounce onto the roof up ahead before something smacks me...
DOUBLE KILL!
Demo count: 45
Now, for world 1-â–ˆ (10-1 or A-1, maybe)...
Need to scroll a little further...
I'll just take this here star. Oh, and I bet I can kill these duders with it, just by jumping on them.
MEGA KILL!
Good, I wasn't ultra unlucky with that. Oh, and there's that "TILOU!" message one more time.
Oh, yes! I can keep going!
Toasty!
It's an underwater 3-4, just like world 1-X. Umm... The game's not gonna reset on me, is it?
Well, did I happen to hit a midpoint?
Oh, great. I'm running out of time. (I think this level only started me with 300 seconds.)
Demo count: 46

Oh, what? Umm... It's a tall wall, and I don't think there are any hidden blocks nearby that'll let me climb over it (I think there would be tell-tale holes in the red water background if there were). I might be able to wall jump over, though...
So, what will world -4 be like?
Yep. Warning: Don't try that if you're not invincible. The game WILL consider you to have hit the ground first before checking for your collision with the koopas, and you'll be the one who gets hurt.
There's also koopas walking along the roof. Uh, oh. I have no control at all while off screen here. I hope I don't land squarely on a koopa!
Next, I'll make my way to the right a bit, so that when I leave here, I'll end up in 1-2's area instead of 1-1's...
Bam! Yes! I knew I could do it! I just had really horrible luck last time!
Hey there, paraduder. How's it going?

Whoa! I just barely avoided that fish right as I went down the pipe there! Okay, so the pipe exits don't work now, but the level can still be cleared thanks to the flagpole beyond the normal exit pipe in this area!
Wait, a springboard? ...No way. Could there possibly be a flagpole here too?
Man, I really wish I could run faster while up here.
T-minus 50 game seconds and counting...
Yeah, I'm gonna drop dead here. Nuts.
So, what will world -2 be like?
...GAAAMMMEEE!!! I hit for 6 fireworks, and they didn't spawn, preventing the game from continuing. Give me a moment...
Whoa, wasn't expecting that to happen. (Sure, now I'm able to clip through a wall that way. Of course, that other time, the "suck"tion was kind of impeding me.)
Ah, there we go. In case you hadn't figured it out yet, this place is normally part of 1-2.
Good thing that fire bar didn't cross the path that Mario automatically walks there, because I think they can still hurt him during that walk (but if I'm wrong, let me know).
Yes! Managed to get here unscathed. Now, as long as I'm not ultra unlucky enough to land squarely on a cheepo as it's at its apex...
Game crash count: 3
Well, it turns out there's a midpoint to this level, but it didn't place me anywhere unusual. Hmm... I'm going to time travel and try something else...
That block had a power up, in case you couldn't tell. Also, I'm pretty sure this level is made from arbitrary data in the game's code, which makes this really interesting.
And 1-Y is done! ...Yeah, it was kind of uneventful.
Alright, time for 1-Y (9-2, I guess)!
Sure, let's get some more fireworks going here.
Maybe I can get lucky and dodge all the cheepos somehow? But, even if I do, I'll never really complete this level, because the exit pipe will just reset the room!
Huzzah! Wow, that was a rather interesting solution to my problem!
Oh, that's interesting... Okay, this isn't specifically what I was trying to do, but I might be able to make this work!
Space-time rewind count: 23
That's okay. I've got a plan to get through the wall to the right of the axe.
Assuming I'm on my "Abra A GAME" here, I should be able to duck-swim into the corner and hopefully clip through the wall.
Wow, really? I managed to mess up the timing on that?
Nuts. Missed the fireworks due to me landing practically on top of the flagpole, but maybe that's a good thing, since there's no chance of the game getting stuck here now.
Yeah, I'm not gonna bother with trying to enter any of the other pipes in this level.
So, let's reset and do the other thing that I was originally intending to do today.
I still don't know exactly what keeps the fireworks from spawning and halting the game like that. I just know that avoiding lining up the timer's ones digit for fireworks lets me avoid that glitch.
Oh, yeah. This coin block in here is much easier to reach now.
Oh, but the suction effect from the pit below might screw this up...
Cool, a 1-up. And here's a floating pipe.
Bouncing off the springboard correctly would help.
...Umm... What? The game hasn't reset on me yet?
No need to waste time with things like that risky 1-up down there.
This is going to make it even trickier to attempt to wall jump. At least I can burninate the spinies...
It seemed like there was something odd about Lakitu's hitbox there, but whatever. I got him.
